==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pulverize
<hw>Pul"ver*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pulverized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pulverizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>pulv⟦eacute⟧riser</ets>, L. <ets>pulverizare</ets>, fr.
<ets>pulvis</ets> dust, powder. See <er>Powder</er>.]</ety> <def>To
reduce of fine powder or dust, as by beating, grinding, or the like;
<as>as, friable substances may be <ex>pulverized</ex> by grinding or
beating, but to <ex>pulverize</ex> malleable bodies other methods must
be pursued</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pulverize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pulverize
<hw>Pul"ver*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become reduced to powder;
to fall to dust; <as>as, the stone <ex>pulverizes</ex>
easily</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pulverizer</ent>⟦br⟧
